				<h3></h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Oct 17th, '04, 12:20</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>Sylphan</strong></div>
				<div class="content">This is a nice complete guide.  That's needed for the tradeskiller, but it's not so much for the non-tradeskiller.
<br />
<br />Since it's so complete, it requires good reading comprehension.  For instance, at the beginning you say "Get a tradeskillable augment, Trean Flies OR Slugworms (depending on the augment), and Dust of Discord OR Discordant Scoriae (depending on if you want the second best or the best type of augment)."  This sentence requires parsing commas, AND operators, and OR operators.  It would be simpler if this sentence was broken out into three seperate bullet points.
<br />
<br />Also, when a guide is this long people tend to cut-and-paste the charts out of it.  So the note about flowstones needing slugworms and others needing trean flies should be incorporated into the list of stones, so it's not easily seperated.
<br />
<br />Finally, it's not a good idea to talk about 'best focus effect' and 'second-best focus effects'.  This is vague at best, but actually quite misleading when compared to Time focuses that offer much more than 15% bonuses.  Just be more specific, call them focus 5 and focus 4 effects.</div>
			</div>
			<hr />
		
