				<h3></h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Oct 18th, '04, 09:32</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>Bellanfear</strong></div>
				<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>Sylphan wrote:</cite>Since it's so complete, it requires good reading comprehension.  For instance, at the beginning you say "Get a tradeskillable augment, Trean Flies OR Slugworms (depending on the augment), and Dust of Discord OR Discordant Scoriae (depending on if you want the second best or the best type of augment)."  This sentence requires parsing commas, AND operators, and OR operators.  It would be simpler if this sentence was broken out into three seperate bullet points.</div></blockquote>That sentence was specifically designed for halflings with no attention span.  If you are not a halfling with no attention span, it may not make sense to you.<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div>Also, when a guide is this long people tend to cut-and-paste the charts out of it.  So the note about flowstones needing slugworms and others needing trean flies should be incorporated into the list of stones, so it's not easily seperated.</div></blockquote>There are <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/eq/showthread.php?t=18403" class="postlink">more informative charts here</a> for you to cut and past.  (This link is also linked in my guide, btw.)  I was more interested in making a guide than a chart, so if you want a chart, I'm afraid you will be disappointed.<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div>Finally, it's not a good idea to talk about 'best focus effect' and 'second-best focus effects'.  This is vague at best, but actually quite misleading when compared to Time focuses that offer much more than 15% bonuses.  Just be more specific, call them focus 5 and focus 4 effects.</div></blockquote>First of all, if you read the 'Mark Descriptions' category, that's where I clarify what 'best' and 'second best' refer to.  Calling them focus 5 and focus 4 was exactly what I wanted to avoid because there are many things you can make that don't fall into that category.  Examples include things like the Mark of Vision which could create Ultravision, Plainsight, or Faerune effects or the Mark of Haste which could give 20%, 30%, or 40% haste.  In fact, refering to them as level 4 and level 5 would really be problematic because melee effects such as Improved Dodge are possible, but only in levels 1, 2, and 3 as opposed to 3, 4, and 5.  Basically, I didn't want to refer to all 15 of the possible effects as level 3, 4, and 5 effects because there are 6 effects where that would be at the best unintelligile and at the worst misleading.  
<br />
<br />Overall, I recommend doing what you want with it.  If you make a better guide, that's less I have to explain to people asking me what to do.   <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":)" title="icon_biggrin.gif" />
<br />
<br /><span style="font-style: italic">edit - I do have plans for updating the guide.  I would like to talk about the slots the augments fit in and prices of the components when I get time.  I expect to have those added sometime this week.</span></div>
